{"aid": "40162610", "title": "Show HN: From SERP to LLM-Ready Data Markdown in Seconds with Firesearch", "url": "https://docs.firecrawl.dev/articles/search-announcement", "domain": "firecrawl.dev", "votes": 6, "user": "cpeffer", "posted_at": "2024-04-25 20:29:40", "comments": 0, "source_title": "Firecrawl Docs", "source_text": "Firecrawl Docs\n\nFirecrawl Docs home page\n\nArticles\n\nIntroducing FireSearch: From SERP to LLM-Ready Data in Seconds\n\nDocumentationAPI Reference\n\n  * Documentation\n\n  * Playground\n\n  * Community\n\n##### Get Started\n\n  * Quickstart\n\n##### SDKs\n\n  * Python SDK\n\n  * Node SDK\n\n  * Langchain\n\n  * Llamaindex\n\n##### Learn\n\n  * Extract website data using LLMs\n\n  * Build a 'Chat with website' using Groq Llama 3\n\n##### Articles\n\n  * Introducing FireSearch: From SERP to LLM-Ready Data in Seconds\n\n##### Contributing\n\n  * Running locally\n\nArticles\n\n# Introducing FireSearch: From SERP to LLM-Ready Data in Seconds\n\nWe are thrilled to announce the beta release of FireSearch, a search +\nextraction API. With /search endpoint, you give Firecrawl a query, it searches\nthe web for the top results, scrape the top pages, and gives you clean\nmarkdown for each so you can feed directly to your LLM.\n\n###\n\nQuick Start Guide\n\nHere\u2019s how you can get started with FireSearch to fetch web content for your\nLLM.\n\nIf you\u2019d like to use our SDKs, you can find the Python SDK here and the Node\nSDK here.\n\n####\n\nStep 1: Crafting Your Search Request\n\nTo execute a search query and receive markdown-formatted content:\n\nCopy\n\n    \n    \n    curl -X POST https://api.firecrawl.dev/v0/search \\ -H 'Content-Type: application/json' \\ -H 'Authorization: Bearer fc-YOUR_API_KEY' \\ -d '{ \"query\": \"your_search_term\", \"pageOptions\": { \"fetchPageContent\": true } }'\n\nReplace fc-YOUR_API_KEY with your actual API key and your_search_term with the\nterm you wish to search for.\n\n####\n\nStep 2: Handling the Response\n\nThe FireSearch API will return search results in markdown format, which you\ncan then readily supply to your LLM for further processing or integration into\nyour system.\n\nCopy\n\n    \n    \n    { \"success\": true, \"data\": [ { \"url\": \"https://www.mendable.ai/\", \"markdown\": \"# Markdown Content of the page\", \"metadata\": { \"title\": \"Mendable | AI for CX and Sales\", \"description\": \"AI for CX and Sales\", \"language\": null, \"sourceURL\": \"https://www.mendable.ai/\" } }, { \"url\": \"https://github.com/mendableai\", \"markdown\": \"# Markdown Content of the page\", \"metadata\": { \"title\": \"Mendable | AI for CX and Sales\", \"description\": \"AI for CX and Sales\", \"language\": null, \"sourceURL\": \"https://www.mendable.ai/\" } }, ] }\n\nIf \"fetchPageContent\": false, data returns faster but without the full page\nmarkdown content.\n\nCopy\n\n    \n    \n    [ { \"title\": \"Example Page Title\", \"url\": \"https://www.example.com\", \"content\": \"# Page Heading\\n\\nContent of the page in markdown format...\" }, // Additional results ]\n\nWe look forward to seeing how FireSearch can power up your projects!\n\n###\n\nCurrent Status:\n\nFireSearch is currently in beta, and we are diligently working to refine and\nimprove its capabilities.\n\nIntegration support for playgrounds and @LangChainAI is on the horizon.\n\nBuild a 'Chat with website' using Groq Llama 3Running locally\n\nxgithublinkedin\n\nPowered by Mintlify\n\n  * Quick Start Guide\n  * Step 1: Crafting Your Search Request\n  * Step 2: Handling the Response\n  * Current Status:\n\n", "frontpage": true}
